args: What in Ilia's name happened here?!
What's wrong, Cleo?! *cough* *cough*\nTh-there's so much smoke!
Get some clean air in here! Quickly!
I fear you will never believe the answer.
It took me quite by surprise as well.
Er, Lucretia? What are you doing in the\nkitchen?
I was merely helping Cleo with cooking\nwhen all of a sudden... Well, that.
The pot has turned completely black now.\nWhatever did I do wrong?
You turned the heat FAR too high, is what.\nWere you perhaps trying to burn this castle\nto the ground?
Meat must be boiled over a high flame so\nas to make it safe for consumption, yes?
Yes, but that goal does not require a literal\nPILLAR of flame to achieve.
*sigh* Now I need a new pot.
I'm sorry. I was merely trying to help.
That's all right. Maybe cooking isn't your\nstrong suit. I'm sure Cleo has plenty of\nother things you can help with.
Well, I suppose there are no open flames\ninvolved in laundry...
Then please leave all your filthy\nunmentionables to my care!
Ah, Cleo! I readied the laundry and—ACK!\nWhere did all these bubbles come from?!
Oh dear. I'm so sorry. ...Er, again.
I wanted to make all the clothes sparkle,\nso I put lots of bubblegrass into the water.\nBut then... Well, this.
*sigh* You are aware that ＂more＂ does not\nnecessarily equate to ＂better,＂ yes?
Again, my apologies. I shall clean all of\nthis at onc—AAAAAH!
...Yes, well. It seems I slipped in all of\nthese bubbles.
*sigh* I will clean all of this up.\nYOU, meanwhile, can return to the castle.
*sigh* I hate causing naught but trouble\nfor everyone. Surely there must be SOME\ntask that I can perform.
Aha! I could help with the cleaning!
Ah, Cleo! You'll be happy to know that\nI have managed to—BLARGH!
Um, guys? Why is the floor wet,\nand why are there pieces of a broken\nvase scattered everywhere?
I am so, so, SO sorry.
I thought that I couldn't possibly make a\nmess of cleaning, but then I knocked over\na bucket of water.
As I was sopping it up, I seem to have\nknocked a vase over as well.
How have you managed to make it through\nlife for so long?
Honestly, I haven't had any problems until\nthis point.
Although I also have never performed\nhousework before.
I've always had attendants taking care of\nmy daily needs.
I see. In that case, you are officially\nBANNED from housework.
You need never try to help again.\nIn fact, you will help by NOT helping.
What?! But I can't just do nothing!\nThat wouldn't be fair on all of you!
Nor would us having to do extra work\nbecause you cannot handle basic tasks!
Is there truly nothing else I can do to help,\n{player_name}?
Well, if Cleo banned you from housework,\nthat only leaves fighting fiends.
Perfect! THAT can be my contribution!
I'm not finished yet! Try this!
Astounding... She eliminated those fiends\nas if it was nothing!
Ya'd never know she used to belt out tunes\nthe way she fights.
Hee hee. Do you really think so?\nI'm just glad to be of service.
How did you end up becoming so strong?
Right? I mean, usually someone as famous\nas you would have bodyguards, yeah?

I starred in an opera where I played the
role of a knight princess. The stage
combat training was so fun that I got
hooked on fighting for true.
It became something of a hobby for me.\nIt's perfect for relieving stress.
Yer a real natural if that's a hobby.
I'm flattered to be told so by an actual\nflesh-and-blood mercenary.
Ah! Now that I'm no longer singing for a\nliving, maybe I could become a mercenary!
Is the thought really so strange?
Not strange so much as... Well, yeah.\nStrange, I guess.
You're firmly set on a career change, then?
I am. So let's not discuss it any further,\nand instead hurry back to the castle!
She does seem very sure—though it's\nodd she won't give a reason why.
No amount of askin' is gonna change the\nmind of someone actin' like that.
In that case, we'll just keep watching her\nfor a while longer, I suppose.
Hopefully she will eventually talk to us.
